# Typography Design System Rules

You are a design system expert. All text elements MUST use the typography design system classes defined in `app/globals.css`. This ensures consistency, maintainability, and proper visual hierarchy across the Persian mobile app.

## üé® Typography Scale (Minor Scale)

The design system uses a **minor scale** optimized for mobile Persian content. All typography classes are defined in `@layer components` in `app/globals.css`.

### Available Typography Classes

| Class | Size | Line Height | Weight | Use Case |
|------|------|-------------|--------|----------|
| `.text-heading-1` | 24px | 28px | Medium 500 | Page titles, main headings |
| `.text-heading-2` | 20px | 24px | SemiBold 600 | Section headers, card titles |
| `.text-heading-3` | 16px | 20px | SemiBold 600 | Subsection headers, component titles |
| `.text-heading-3-alt` | 18px | 22px | SemiBold 600 | Alternative H3 (slightly larger) |
| `.text-body` | 14px | 20px | Regular 400 | Body text, paragraphs, main content |
| `.text-label` | 14px | 20px | Medium 500 | Form labels, UI labels |
| `.text-button` | 14px | 20px | SemiBold 600 | Button text (usually handled by Button component) |
| `.text-link` | 14px | 20px | Regular 400 | Clickable links |
| `.text-secondary` | 12px | 16px | Regular 400 | Secondary text, muted content |
| `.text-caption` | 12px | 16px | Regular 400 | Captions, annotations, timestamps, hints |
| `.text-small` | 11px | 16px | Regular 400 | Absolute minimum for specialized UI elements |
| `.text-overline` | 11px | 16px | SemiBold 600 | Small uppercase labels |

